##Extra | 24 hours after Wuhan's closure

By Suzhou Museum

Editor | Huashi

Introduction

"from 10:00 on January 23,2020, the city's bus, subway, ferry and long-distance passenger services will be suspended. People should not leave Wuhan, the airport and railway stations will be temporarily closed from the Han corridor without special reasons. Recovery time will be announced. Please understand and support US, passengers!"This is a notice from the Wuhan COVID-19 infectious pneumonia prevention and control headquarters. The city of Wuhan closed, caught off guard, the outside world in an uproar. In the city of Wuhan, which has a population of ten million, every ordinary citizen and every ordinary family was anxious, confused, helpless or desperate during the two days that the city was shut down? No one knows. You know, people from Wuhan Fly to Toronto overnight, drive to Yueyang, even Shanghai.

Today, on the eve of the Lunar New Year, entertainment magazine broke the rules by making contact with two students in Wuhan City, a East China Normal University undergraduate Moe and a Soochow University graduate student Su Bo, describe the changes in their ordinary life, their knowledge of the epidemic situation, their intuitive feeling of the epidemic prevention measures, and more importantly, their love for Wuhan.

Moe

I feel like a modern-day biohazard
—————————————

"Wuhan closed city" The news is two o'clock in the morning out, see at that time the whole person directly collapsed. I was born and raised in Wuhan, where almost all my relatives live. Although before see similar news"Wuhan person does not go out, outside person does not come in", but really did not expect to meet suddenly close a city. My most intuitive feeling is fear, fear and helplessness, really worried about the family and friends of each situation, we stay in Wuhan people how to do? How serious is this epidemic really? I had no idea. It was like living through a real raccoon city.

When I woke up the next morning, my mother and I went to the supermarket to stock up on supplies, medicines and supplies. The two of US put on two layers of surgical masks before we left the house, and it was only the day before yesterday that we went to seven pharmacies, had acquaintances, and finally snapped them up. In fact, the N95 masks recommended by experts sell here for 35 yuan each. If you use it for a month, the cost of the mask is more than a thousand, even we can not buy it at all. And Taobao 20 orders mask is still not shipped, express delivery also stopped, do not know when to receive. My mother and I also put on our normal glasses for fear of flying droplets in our eyes (we can't actually buy goggles in Wuhan) and wore gloves to avoid contact with any possible infection. We went out to look in the mirror, i feel like a modern-day biohazard.

My home is in Wuchang District, a long way from the Jiang'an District and Kong Hon districts of Hankou, where the epidemic is worst. Across the river, but people including myself are still in a state of fear, no one can guarantee that he is absolutely safe. The nearest large supermarket to our home is Zhongbai Warehouse, which is about a twenty-minute walk away. Public transport was suspended, there were no subways or buses, and the only way to travel was on foot or by car. I've tried using Didi at home, and it says the wait is at least an hour, which is probably ideal, since many drivers are already reluctant to take orders.

Twenty minutes from home to the supermarket, we walked at a brisk pace. The small shops on the side of the street are almost closed, and you don't see many people and cars passing by. It's like a ghost town, empty, no one to talk to, no cars to speak to, the whole atmosphere makes you speechless. The only few passers-by you can see, should have just snapped up from the supermarket, all wearing masks, carrying several large bags of things, in a hurry to go, do not want to stay a moment. Everyone from two to three meters away, afraid of passing passers-by is the next potential infected. On the way, I ran into someone I knew from the yard. It's kind of funny that we're on opposite sides of the street, wearing thick masks, shouting at each other to be safe and not to wander. I think I've seen this in a horror movie before.

Arrived at the supermarket, found that many people wearing masks in the supermarket there to buy, the overall is very orderly, are in line. It was just vegetables, frozen food, Rice, and toiletries all gone. When my mother and I arrived, the place was empty. We had to go back with three cucumbers, two tomatoes and two tubes of noodles. Everything else was gone. The price of Hongshan District Moss rose from 4 to 5 yuan to more than 30 yuan. The price of Chinese cabbage rose to 12 yuan per catty. It was probably the first day of the siege in Wuhan, and everything was so sudden, and everyone was in a panic, and everyone was stocking up like crazy, and everyone was going to stock up about a week's worth of food in advance to avoid going out. Stay at home brush friends circle, see a classmate issued Jianghan road and Han Street photos. It used to be the two most lively places in Wuhan, but now there is no one here. Parents at home, always remind you: "Do not go out, stay at home. ". This kind of atmosphere, let me every time go out all the more nervous, for fear of what accident. At home, the New Year's Eve dinner, New Year's greetings are canceled. I live in the yard also set up a "Wuhan Pneumonia Prevention Group, " the registration of staff and out of the registration. The wechat group is bombarded with news of Wuhan Pneumonia: The situation of the hospital, the situation of the highway blockade, and how many people have been diagnosed, and who has been isolated in the community inside.

My mother told me that her colleague's son had gone to the hospital for several days with a cough and fever, but could not be diagnosed at all. He waited from nine in the morning until after twelve in the evening, and then had to go home to be quarantined. Or someone told me how many people had been diagnosed in Concorde hospital, how many patients could not be treated in seven hospitals, there were too many people waiting in line. Or maybe I'm at home, and I hear an ambulance honking outside, and I panic, and that's what's really going on around me. Then there was a time, I do not want to see micro-blog, Wechat, see once will panic a time, sad, want to cry, helpless. In such a situation, the city, nerves are particularly nervous, I do not know what to believe, believe who. All we can do is encourage each other and protect ourselves.

Sometimes I wonder, if we had started paying attention on the 18th or even the beginning of January, would things be different now? The first time to parents issued Wuhan Pneumonia News, or just out at the end of December, tell them to be careful. However, Wuhan or with a peaceful atmosphere of the New Year, the Party of the Party, the shopping, the meal of the meal, who did not take this seriously. Remember January 18 I returned to Wuhan Station, the entire station basically no one wearing masks, except me and my partner. I was surprised that everyone looked at us as if we were different. By then the news had already reported that someone had contracted the same new type of pneumonia abroad. Was the outbreak really under control? I took the subway on the 19th and found that not everyone in the subway was wearing a mask. At dinner that day, relatives told me not to worry, I was just too nervous, no one will be infected, Wuhan has no human-to-human transmission, we have not been to the south China seafood market.

In the isolated island of Wuhan, we will protect ourselves, isolate ourselves, just hope we do not give up on us, I live 19 years of place, this time also want to accompany you through, Wuhan refueling.

Subo

The aunt put the food at the door and shouted, "don't open it. I'm leaving. "
——————————————————

On the 11th, I traveled from Suzhou to Zhuhai and Macau. On the 17th, I originally intended to fly directly from Guangdong to Chongqing. From the oft-mentioned "epidemic situation can be prevented and controlled" and "limited human-to-human transmission" , I concluded that the epidemic was not serious. So I chose to go back to Wuhan to catch up with my friends, and as soon as I arrived in Wuhan, the sudden change of situation in the next two days told me that this time the outbreak in Wuhan had become a little out of control. I returned my ticket home to Chongqing and gave up the journey home. From Chongqing to Wuhan: 303 Km, about 4 hours, the route has been used many times. It's not that I don't want to go home. The tradition of New Year's reunions has been taken for granted for the past twenty or three years, but for the sake of my family's safety, and for the sake of the long term reunion that will follow, I've made up my mind to stay behind, just before the city closes down.

The day before New Year's Eve in 2019, I was in Suzhou, the first time I knew of the new pneumonia in Wuhan. In a chat with friends, I learned that although the day in the subway to prepare for the new year is still a lot of people, but many young people have put on a mask just. Feel at that time pneumonia, just a stone on the surface of the water, fell into the water with a ripple on the direct sink down. On New Year's Day in 2020, young people in the streets of Wuhan took off their masks. Academician Zhong Nanshan's announcement on January 21 marked a turning point in the epidemic. The day before, I was wearing a PM 2.5 mask and going out with my friends to scan the stalls, totally unaware of the seriousness of the problem. In the early morning of the 21st, my friend mentioned in the wechat group that his grandfather was taken to the hospital for diagnosis because he had a fever and cough. His grandfather's condition could not be confirmed at a crowded hospital. In case my friend got infected, his parents asked him to move in with his aunt, who lives just across the street from me, so I thought I'd invite him to stay with me.

At two o'clock in the morning, my friend knocked on my door. He couldn't stop crying the moment he came in. It was the first time I saw him cry. In order to protect him from the outbreak, his parents stood in the dark and cold in the early hours of the morning, waiting for him to pack his bags and did not dare to go upstairs. The short flight of stairs seemed so long because of fear, and so close because of love. I didn't know what to do. It was too short. Just one night, the friends who had been there, who were supposed to be celebrating the arrival of the New Year, had to stop and face this unprecedented, unknown, terrible epidemic.

Fortunately, since the 21st, my friends and I stayed in this temporary "safe house" , has not been out. Because my parents are far away in Chongqing, my only relatives in Wuhan are my aunt's family and aunt's family. My neighbors took good care of me, bringing me dumplings and meatballs, which tasted like New Year's food, and would come up to see me every day to make sure I was safe. Under the ice-cold data, the covered individual and the individual help each other, has become that ice and Snow Day was lit the match. My aunt also took the risk, sent a lotus root folder and braised beef, when they just put it outside the door, "viciously" stressed that I must not open the door. It used to be "you're here, happy New Year" , but now it's "don't open it, I'm leaving" .

During my three days in the safe house, I kept up with the developments of the epidemic and fought the rumors in panic. Every time I see the relevant prevention methods will hold the "better to believe that there is, not to believe that no" mentality to forward to friends and relatives. While rumors are flying around, we can't escape the artillery bombardment of the dark region. "people in Wuhan are taking anti-fever medicine to get out of the city" and "a new type of pneumonia patient has fled from a hospital in Wuhan" are also frequent topics on Weibo.

My parents returned to Chongqing in mid November to take care of their grandparents. While traveling in Macau, my father reminded me of the severity of the Wuhan outbreak and called me several times to fly directly from Guangdong to Chongqing and not to return to Wuhan. I was determined to go back to Wuhan, but also complained a few words. My Dad's still mad at me about it. This misjudgment, it was the information that blinded me. On the 23rd, I was locked in Wuhan because of the closure of the city, which was the time for the family to take care of me. Early on the morning of the 23rd, I drove back to Jingmen from Wuhan with many friends. It seemed safer outside the city than inside.

Relatives in Chongqing, only through the wechat video, and family members together to eat the cloud of New Year's Eve: one side of the hotel with the standard reunion dinner, while my friends and I on the cabbage shabu fat hot pot. It was a happy reunion after all.

I would like to say that Wuhan has been under heavy pressure, our traffic has been blocked, but do not use accusations, abuse, contempt, ridicule words sealed our hearts.

I have always loved every tree and Bush in Wuhan. This city has given me so many memories that it is an indispensable part of who I am today. Hope that those tired of the health care workers pay to break the epidemic in return, the whole community masks, supplies donations such as a warm current is flowing into Wuhan, Wuhan, may be able to overcome the epidemic as soon as possible. I believe that April, Wuhan Cherry Blossoms are still gorgeous.

(instructor: Wu Changchang)

Or someone told me how many people had been diagnosed in Concorde hospital, how many patients could not be treated in seven hospitals, there were too many people waiting in line. Or maybe I'm at home, and I hear an ambulance honking outside, and I panic, and that's what's really going on around me. Then there was a time, I do not want to see micro-blog, Wechat, see once will panic a time, sad, want to cry, helpless. In such a situation, the city, nerves are particularly nervous, I do not know what to believe, believe who. All we can do is encourage each other and protect ourselves.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Sometimes I wonder, if we had started paying attention on the 18th or even the beginning of January, would things be different now? The first time to parents issued Wuhan Pneumonia News, or just out at the end of December, tell them to be careful. However, Wuhan or with a peaceful atmosphere of the New Year, the Party of the Party, the shopping, the meal of the meal, who did not take this seriously. Remember January 18 I returned to Wuhan Station, the entire station basically no one wearing masks, except me and my partner. I was surprised that everyone looked at us as if we were different. By then the news had already reported that someone had contracted the same new type of pneumonia abroad. Was the outbreak really under control? I took the subway on the 19th and found that not everyone in the subway was wearing a mask. At dinner that day, relatives told me not to worry, I was just too nervous, no one will be infected, Wuhan has no human-to-human transmission, we have not been to the south China seafood market.

In the isolated island of Wuhan, we will protect ourselves, isolate ourselves, just hope we do not give up on us, I live 19 years of place, this time also want to accompany you through, Wuhan refueling.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Subo

The aunt put the food at the door and shouted, "don't open it. I'm leaving. "

——————————————————

On the 11th, I traveled from Suzhou to Zhuhai and Macau. On the 17th, I originally intended to fly directly from Guangdong to Chongqing. From the oft-mentioned "epidemic situation can be prevented and controlled" and "limited human-to-human transmission" , I concluded that the epidemic was not serious. So I chose to go back to Wuhan to catch up with my friends, and as soon as I arrived in Wuhan, the sudden change of situation in the next two days told me that this time the outbreak in Wuhan had become a little out of control. I returned my ticket home to Chongqing and gave up the journey home. From Chongqing to Wuhan: 303 Km, about 4 hours, the route has been used many times. It's not that I don't want to go home. The tradition of New Year's reunions has been taken for granted for the past twenty or three years, but for the sake of my family's safety, and for the sake of the long term reunion that will follow, I've made up my mind to stay behind, just before the city closes down.

The day before New Year's Eve in 2019, I was in Suzhou, the first time I knew of the new pneumonia in Wuhan. In a chat with friends, I learned that although the day in the subway to prepare for the new year is still a lot of people, but many young people have put on a mask just. Feel at that time pneumonia, just a stone on the surface of the water, fell into the water with a ripple on the direct sink down. On New Year's Day in 2020, young people in the streets of Wuhan took off their masks. Academician Zhong Nanshan's announcement on January 21 marked a turning point in the epidemic. The day before, I was wearing a PM 2.5 mask and going out with my friends to scan the stalls, totally unaware of the seriousness of the problem. In the early morning of the 21st, my friend mentioned in the wechat group that his grandfather was taken to the hospital for diagnosis because he had a fever and cough. His grandfather's condition could not be confirmed at a crowded hospital. In case my friend got infected, his parents asked him to move in with his aunt, who lives just across the street from me, so I thought I'd invite him to stay with me.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At two o'clock in the morning, my friend knocked on my door. He couldn't stop crying the moment he came in. It was the first time I saw him cry. In order to protect him from the outbreak, his parents stood in the dark and cold in the early hours of the morning, waiting for him to pack his bags and did not dare to go upstairs. The short flight of stairs seemed so long because of fear, and so close because of love. I didn't know what to do. It was too short. Just one night, the friends who had been there, who were supposed to be celebrating the arrival of the New Year, had to stop and face this unprecedented, unknown, terrible epidemic.

Fortunately, since the 21st, my friends and I stayed in this temporary "safe house" , has not been out. Because my parents are far away in Chongqing, my only relatives in Wuhan are my aunt's family and aunt's family. My neighbors took good care of me, bringing me dumplings and meatballs, which tasted like New Year's food, and would come up to see me every day to make sure I was safe. Under the ice-cold data, the covered individual and the individual help each other, has become that ice and Snow Day was lit the match. My aunt also took the risk, sent a lotus root folder and braised beef, when they just put it outside the door, "viciously" stressed that I must not open the door. It used to be "you're here, happy New Year" , but now it's "don't open it, I'm leaving" .

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
During my three days in the safe house, I kept up with the developments of the epidemic and fought the rumors in panic. Every time I see the relevant prevention methods will hold the "better to believe that there is, not to believe that no" mentality to forward to friends and relatives. While rumors are flying around, we can't escape the artillery bombardment of the dark region. "people in Wuhan are taking anti-fever medicine to get out of the city" and "a new type of pneumonia patient has fled from a hospital in Wuhan" are also frequent topics on Weibo.

My parents returned to Chongqing in mid November to take care of their grandparents. While traveling in Macau, my father reminded me of the severity of the Wuhan outbreak and called me several times to fly directly from Guangdong to Chongqing and not to return to Wuhan. I was determined to go back to Wuhan, but also complained a few words. My Dad's still mad at me about it. This misjudgment, it was the information that blinded me. On the 23rd, I was locked in Wuhan because of the closure of the city, which was the time for the family to take care of me. Early on the morning of the 23rd, I drove back to Jingmen from Wuhan with many friends. It seemed safer outside the city than inside.

Relatives in Chongqing, only through the wechat video, and family members together to eat the cloud of New Year's Eve: one side of the hotel with the standard reunion dinner, while my friends and I on the cabbage shabu fat hot pot. It was a happy reunion after all.

I would like to say that Wuhan has been under heavy pressure, our traffic has been blocked, but do not use accusations, abuse, contempt, ridicule words sealed our hearts.

I have always loved every tree and Bush in Wuhan. This city has given me so many memories that it is an indispensable part of who I am today. Hope that those tired of the health care workers pay to break the epidemic in return, the whole community masks, supplies donations such as a warm current is flowing into Wuhan, Wuhan, may be able to overcome the epidemic as soon as possible. I believe that April, Wuhan Cherry Blossoms are still gorgeous.
